WEBVTT

00:01.269 --> 00:03.854
Professor Gerard, I came
to ask for a favor.

00:03.939 --> 00:04.939
The answer's no.

00:04.939 --> 00:06.474
Which is why
I brought this.

00:06.558 --> 00:07.775
You know.

00:07.893 --> 00:09.026
And you talk a big game,

00:09.111 --> 00:11.062
but you're just as human
as everyone else,

00:11.196 --> 00:12.313
you smug son of a bitch.

00:12.447 --> 00:14.448
Louis.

00:14.566 --> 00:16.200
- What are you doing here?
- Leaving.

00:16.318 --> 00:18.819
That way, I don't have to look
at either one of you two liars.

00:18.954 --> 00:20.788
[door opens, slams]

00:20.906 --> 00:23.124
Oh, my God.
He knows.

00:23.241 --> 00:25.626
He doesn't just know.

00:25.744 --> 00:26.961
He's a name partner.

00:27.079 --> 00:28.719
(Louis) She came to me
and lied to my face.

00:28.747 --> 00:30.664
She did it to protect me.

00:30.799 --> 00:32.466
I'm gonna keep
hammering on her

00:32.584 --> 00:33.834
until you break.

00:33.969 --> 00:35.920
(Jessica) With a new name
comes a new beginning.

00:36.054 --> 00:37.972
Here's to our newest
name partner,

00:38.090 --> 00:39.090
Louis Litt.

00:39.091 --> 00:40.091
[applause]

00:40.142 --> 00:41.642
(Jeff)
Louis has something on you.

00:41.760 --> 00:45.846
Daniel Hardman embezzled
money from the firm,

00:45.931 --> 00:47.231
and I covered it up.

00:47.349 --> 00:49.400
Why couldn't you trust me
with this before?

00:49.484 --> 00:51.185
Because I didn't know
how you'd react.

00:51.269 --> 00:54.488
Jessica, your secret
is safe with me.

01:00.362 --> 01:03.247
[jazzy music]

01:03.365 --> 01:11.255
♪ ♪

01:16.428 --> 01:19.263
I thought we were done
with rooftop conversations.

01:19.381 --> 01:20.965
Some things
require privacy.

01:21.049 --> 01:23.089
I haven't heard you say that
since the midnight coup

01:23.135 --> 01:24.468
of Schmidt, Gordon,
and Van Dyke.

01:24.603 --> 01:25.469
You done?

01:25.554 --> 01:26.554
It wasn't a joke.

01:26.605 --> 01:27.605
Well, neither is this.

01:27.639 --> 01:29.640
I told Jeff Malone
I helped cover up

01:29.775 --> 01:32.193
Daniel Hardman's
embezzlement.

01:32.310 --> 01:34.195
Why the hell would you
open that time capsule?

01:34.312 --> 01:35.613
Because he knew
the explanation

01:35.730 --> 01:37.731
we gave the partners about
Louis was bullshit,

01:37.866 --> 01:38.983
and I had to tell him
something.

01:39.067 --> 01:41.068
You could've told him
it was none of his business.

01:41.153 --> 01:42.736
Harvey, I didn't
bring you here

01:42.871 --> 01:44.155
to get relationship advice.

01:44.289 --> 01:45.623
I brought you here
to tell you what I did

01:45.707 --> 01:46.707
in case it ever came up.

01:46.708 --> 01:47.708
No, you didn't.

01:47.709 --> 01:48.659
You brought me here
because now

01:48.794 --> 01:50.114
you have to get Louis
to back you,

01:50.128 --> 01:51.579
and you knew
you'd be mad at me

01:51.663 --> 01:53.423
when I told you what
you didn't want to hear.

01:53.465 --> 01:54.945
You're right.
I don't want to hear it.

01:55.000 --> 01:56.167
How do you think
it's gonna go

01:56.301 --> 01:57.334
when I tell Louis
he holds

01:57.502 --> 01:59.637
the fate of my relationship
in his hands?

01:59.721 --> 02:00.888
How do you think
it's gonna go

02:01.006 --> 02:03.057
the first time Malone
brings up Louis' blackmail?

02:03.175 --> 02:04.225
I don't care.

02:04.342 --> 02:05.309
Well, I'll tell you
how it's gonna go.

02:05.393 --> 02:06.811
Louis is gonna look back

02:06.895 --> 02:09.513
with his beady little eyes
and say, "Embezzlement?

02:09.598 --> 02:11.515
That's not how I got
my name on the wall."

02:11.600 --> 02:13.684
And the shit's gonna
hit the fan anyway.

02:13.819 --> 02:14.852
You know what?

02:14.986 --> 02:16.103
You can be a real
son of a bitch.

02:16.188 --> 02:18.072
Yeah, but instead
of being pissed at me,

02:18.190 --> 02:19.273
why don't you take
a look in the mirror?

02:19.357 --> 02:21.158
Because we held out
an olive branch,

02:21.243 --> 02:22.693
and after Louis hears this,

02:22.828 --> 02:24.195
he's gonna take that branch

02:24.279 --> 02:25.863
and beat the shit
out of us with it.

02:33.205 --> 02:35.372
[elevator bell dings]

02:35.540 --> 02:37.208
Louis.

02:37.292 --> 02:39.210
Professor Gerard?
What are you doing here?

02:39.344 --> 02:40.544
I've got a small
legal matter

02:40.679 --> 02:41.762
to attend to.

02:41.880 --> 02:43.714
Well, is it anything
I can help you with?

02:43.849 --> 02:45.409
Actually, I'm here
to speak with Harvey.

02:45.433 --> 02:46.800
Ah, ah, I understand.

02:46.885 --> 02:48.219
You're looking
for a name partner.

02:48.303 --> 02:49.436
Well, you can't quite
see it from here,

02:49.554 --> 02:50.554
but if you walk back
about ten feet,

02:50.689 --> 02:51.805
take a gander to your left,

02:51.890 --> 02:53.190
you'll see I've gotten
a little recognition--

02:53.308 --> 02:55.059
I appreciate that,
but as I said,

02:55.227 --> 02:57.278
I'm here to speak
with Harvey.

03:01.283 --> 03:03.067
(Mike) So are we gonna talk about
that little welcome speech

03:03.201 --> 03:04.401
that Jessica
made for Louis?

03:04.536 --> 03:05.703
(Harvey) We don't have
to talk about it

03:05.787 --> 03:07.705
because Louis isn't
going to accept it.

03:07.789 --> 03:08.906
Why not?

03:08.990 --> 03:10.350
Because it'll be
a cold day in hell

03:10.408 --> 03:12.409
when he can accept being
Maverick to my Iceman.

03:12.577 --> 03:14.745
Don't--don't you mean
Iceman to your Maverick?

03:14.829 --> 03:16.247
No, I don't.

03:16.381 --> 03:18.883
You actually want to be
Iceman over Maverick?

03:19.000 --> 03:20.501
- Who got the trophy?
- Who's the better pilot?

03:20.635 --> 03:21.802
- The one who got the trophy.
- Wrong.

03:21.920 --> 03:23.921
Because in the end,
Maverick saved Iceman,

03:24.055 --> 03:25.422
and if he hadn't, trophy boy
would be sitting

03:25.590 --> 03:27.725
on the bottom
of the Indian Ocean right now.

03:27.842 --> 03:29.593
- Where he'd still be the man.
- According to you.

03:29.728 --> 03:32.096
According to me is the only
"according to" that matters.

03:32.230 --> 03:33.097
Here we go.

03:33.181 --> 03:35.766
(Gerard)
Maybe, but according to me,

03:35.901 --> 03:38.435
Viper was the real hero
of that film.

03:38.520 --> 03:39.937
What?

03:40.021 --> 03:41.572
You think I'm too old
to know <i> Top Gun?</i>

03:41.656 --> 03:43.107
What I think is,
you have no business

03:43.275 --> 03:44.325
being in my office.

03:44.442 --> 03:46.322
Are we gonna do this
in front of your associate?

03:46.411 --> 03:48.195
We don't have to do anything
in front of anybody.

03:48.280 --> 03:50.197
You just have to go.

03:52.751 --> 03:54.785
Harvey...

03:54.869 --> 03:56.120
I need a lawyer.

03:56.254 --> 03:57.454
Louis' office
is down the hall.

03:57.539 --> 03:59.456
I don't want Louis.

03:59.624 --> 04:00.874
- I want you.
- That's funny.

04:01.009 --> 04:02.543
The last time you saw me,
you told me I wasn't fit

04:02.677 --> 04:04.545
to practice law
in your ivory tower.

04:04.629 --> 04:05.796
What I told you was,

04:05.931 --> 04:08.132
is that you'll sacrifice
ethics for wins,

04:08.216 --> 04:10.768
and right now
I'm not in my ivory tower,

04:10.852 --> 04:11.852
and I need a win.

04:11.970 --> 04:12.970
I knew it.

04:12.971 --> 04:14.021
You're just like
everybody else.

04:14.139 --> 04:15.379
The ends don't
justify the means

04:15.440 --> 04:16.807
until it's your ass
on the line.

04:16.891 --> 04:18.858
Do you think I like
asking you for help?

04:18.976 --> 04:21.562
I think this Liberty Rail thing
must have you by the balls.

04:21.646 --> 04:22.646
So you know.

04:22.731 --> 04:23.731
I know after their
train derailed,

04:23.865 --> 04:24.945
you were appointed
to assess

04:24.983 --> 04:26.817
the victims'
compensation formula,

04:26.985 --> 04:28.035
and I know after you did,

04:28.153 --> 04:29.620
some of those victims
hired a lawyer

04:29.738 --> 04:31.288
and opened
an investigation.

04:31.373 --> 04:32.706
Then you also know
they found nothing.

04:32.824 --> 04:34.742
(Mike) Then the question is,
why are you here?

04:34.826 --> 04:37.628
The TSA found $25,000
in my luggage

04:37.712 --> 04:40.581
the day I announced I was
changing the formula.

04:40.715 --> 04:41.999
So now you're
being accused

04:42.133 --> 04:43.217
of accepting
a bribe.

04:43.335 --> 04:44.752
Which I did not do.

04:44.836 --> 04:46.837
(Harvey) Well, good luck proving
that, Professor,

04:46.972 --> 04:48.839
because it won't be
with my help.

04:50.976 --> 04:53.510
I was wrong about you,
Mr. Specter.

04:53.595 --> 04:55.262
I never thought that you
wouldn't represent somebody

04:55.347 --> 04:56.397
just because you
didn't like them.

04:56.514 --> 04:57.681
Well, you're wrong again.

04:57.849 --> 04:59.850
I don't like you,
but I'm not representing you

05:00.018 --> 05:01.485
because you did
something shady,

05:01.603 --> 05:03.153
and I'm not screwing over
crash victims

05:03.271 --> 05:04.321
for the likes of you.

05:04.406 --> 05:05.489
You know I didn't do this.

05:05.607 --> 05:07.574
What I know is
you showed yourself in.

05:07.692 --> 05:09.410
You can show yourself out.

05:15.283 --> 05:18.869
(man) ♪ See the money,
wanna stay for your meal ♪

05:19.004 --> 05:22.206
♪ Get another piece of pie
for your wife ♪

05:22.340 --> 05:25.376
♪ Everybody wanna know
how it feel ♪

05:25.510 --> 05:29.129
♪ Everybody wanna see
what it's like ♪

05:29.264 --> 05:32.049
♪ I'll even eat a bean pie,
I don't mind ♪

05:32.183 --> 05:36.053
♪ Me and Missy is
so busy, busy making money ♪

05:36.187 --> 05:37.521
♪ All right ♪

05:37.523 --> 05:39.142
♪ All step back,
I'm 'bout to dance ♪

05:39.143 --> 05:43.143
<font color=#00FF00>♪ Suits 4x12 ♪</font>
<font color=#00FFFF>Respect</font>
