05:43.144 --> 05:44.812
♪ The greenback boogie ♪

05:44.836 --> 05:51.068
== sync, corrected by <font color=#00FF00>elderman</font> ==
<font color=#00FFFF>@elder_man</font>

05:51.069 --> 05:52.119
Hey, I didn't want
to say anything

05:52.237 --> 05:53.904
in front of Gerard,
but has it occurred to you

05:53.988 --> 05:56.156
that you're an idiot
if you don't take this case?

05:56.291 --> 05:57.908
Last year, you were
shitting yourself

05:57.992 --> 05:59.042
he'd find out about you,

05:59.160 --> 06:00.800
and now you think
we should work with him?

06:00.879 --> 06:02.379
No, I wasn't worried
he'd find out.

06:02.497 --> 06:04.081
I was worried about Louis.

06:04.215 --> 06:05.966
Gerard didn't bat
an eye at me back then,

06:06.084 --> 06:07.417
and he didn't just now.

06:07.552 --> 06:08.585
But we get him
out of this

06:08.720 --> 06:10.220
and he ever does
find out about me,

06:10.338 --> 06:11.421
he's gonna owe us.

06:11.556 --> 06:14.091
Mike, that man is never
gonna compromise his ethics

06:14.225 --> 06:15.665
just because we got him
out of a jam.

06:15.677 --> 06:16.997
Never gonna compromise
his ethics?

06:17.095 --> 06:18.312
You just said
he took a bribe.

06:18.429 --> 06:20.109
So what does that
have to do with anything?

06:21.399 --> 06:22.919
It has everything
to do with everything

06:22.934 --> 06:25.352
because you don't
think he did it.

06:25.487 --> 06:27.187
[chuckles]

06:27.322 --> 06:28.605
- So what?
- So what?

06:28.740 --> 06:29.940
That means you're not
turning him down

06:30.074 --> 06:31.275
because you think
he's shady.

06:31.409 --> 06:32.526
You're...

06:32.660 --> 06:33.911
You're turning him down
because you have

06:34.028 --> 06:36.029
a Henry Gerard-sized chip
on your shoulder.

06:36.114 --> 06:37.698
I do not have a chip
on my shoulder.

06:37.832 --> 06:39.166
You sure sound
like you do,

06:39.284 --> 06:40.367
which makes you
worse than an idiot.

06:40.502 --> 06:41.502
It makes you a jackass.

06:41.586 --> 06:43.003
- Excuse me?
- You heard me.

06:43.121 --> 06:44.705
You know that he divided
that money fairly,

06:44.789 --> 06:45.706
which means that
you're just--

06:45.790 --> 06:47.174
I don't care
what it means,

06:47.292 --> 06:48.458
and I don't need
a lecture from you.

06:48.593 --> 06:49.593
Apparently you do,

06:49.677 --> 06:50.677
because you're about
to screw over

06:50.795 --> 06:52.045
a bunch of innocent people

06:52.130 --> 06:54.848
just to stick it to some guy
who hurt your feelings.

06:54.966 --> 06:56.433
That's not something
I ever thought

06:56.551 --> 06:57.935
I'd be saying to you.

07:00.939 --> 07:02.806
Well, look who it is,

07:02.891 --> 07:04.858
the woman who put me
in my place.

07:04.976 --> 07:05.976
What now?

07:06.060 --> 07:07.060
You want me to sign
a piece of paper

07:07.145 --> 07:08.695
admitting that I was the man
on the grassy knoll?

07:08.813 --> 07:10.647
I meant what I said
at the ceremony, Louis.

07:10.782 --> 07:12.302
You mean the ceremony
that you only had

07:12.317 --> 07:13.534
in order to trick me?

07:13.651 --> 07:15.485
I had it because
you demanded it,

07:15.620 --> 07:17.487
but I'm not here
to talk about that.

07:17.622 --> 07:18.982
I'm here to talk
about Jeff Malone.

07:19.040 --> 07:20.040
What about him?

07:20.074 --> 07:21.325
You may be aware
that he and I are--

07:21.459 --> 07:23.076
<i>Fifty Shades of Grey?</i>
I'm aware.

07:23.161 --> 07:25.495
I'm gonna let that go

07:25.630 --> 07:27.748
because you may
also not be aware

07:27.832 --> 07:29.132
that I had to lie to him.

07:33.922 --> 07:35.472
He doesn't know
about Mike, does he?

07:35.590 --> 07:37.007
No.

07:37.091 --> 07:38.642
But he does know
you committed a crime

07:38.760 --> 07:39.760
and that you resigned

07:39.844 --> 07:41.345
and now your name
is up on the wall.

07:41.429 --> 07:42.429
What'd you tell him?

07:42.513 --> 07:45.098
I told him you found out
that I covered up

07:45.183 --> 07:46.767
Daniel Hardman's
embezzlement

07:46.851 --> 07:49.186
and that you used it
to strong-arm me.

07:49.270 --> 07:51.688
And now you want me to protect
another one of your secrets.

07:51.856 --> 07:53.991
It's the same secret,
Louis,

07:54.108 --> 07:55.859
and you have just as much
invested in it as I do.

07:55.944 --> 07:57.224
No, I don't,
because I don't care

07:57.278 --> 07:59.246
if your relationship
with Jeff survives or not.

08:01.282 --> 08:02.416
What do you want, Louis?

08:02.533 --> 08:04.534
I want something for
continuing to cover your ass.

08:04.669 --> 08:07.304
You got something.
You got your name on the wall.

08:07.405 --> 08:09.045
Now I want the respect
that comes with it.

08:09.090 --> 08:10.207
Meaning?

08:10.291 --> 08:13.043
I want one
of Harvey's clients.

08:13.177 --> 08:14.177
Which one?

08:17.048 --> 08:18.548
That's between me
and Harvey.

08:18.716 --> 08:21.551
[rock music]

08:21.719 --> 08:29.559
♪ ♪

08:31.000 --> 08:37.073
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

08:39.988 --> 08:41.621
Okay.

08:41.739 --> 08:43.907
I agreed to meet.

08:43.991 --> 08:45.712
I hope it's not just
so you can tell me more

08:45.743 --> 08:48.211
about what a horrible
person I am.

08:48.329 --> 08:50.714
I came here to tell you
that I changed my mind.

08:50.798 --> 08:53.717
So you admitted to yourself
that I didn't do this?

08:53.835 --> 08:55.385
I've admitted to myself
that you came to me

08:55.503 --> 08:57.838
because this case
needs rule-bending,

08:57.922 --> 09:02.059
and you're gonna tell me
why right now.

09:02.143 --> 09:03.727
The money.

09:03.845 --> 09:05.178
Yes, the money.

09:05.313 --> 09:06.430
If you weren't bribed,

09:06.564 --> 09:08.849
where the hell did you
get that $25,000 from?

09:08.933 --> 09:10.567
You know where it
came from.

09:10.652 --> 09:11.768
It's the same thing
you tried to use

09:11.903 --> 09:13.520
to blackmail me last year.

09:13.655 --> 09:15.656
Let me get this
straight.

09:15.773 --> 09:16.940
You have an explanation
for the money

09:17.075 --> 09:18.358
that would get you
out of this whole thing.

09:18.443 --> 09:22.579
But I can't use it.

09:22.664 --> 09:24.114
Where are you going?

09:24.248 --> 09:26.166
To get you out of this.

09:26.284 --> 09:28.251
Welcome to the real world,
Professor.

09:28.369 --> 09:31.254
[rock music]

09:31.372 --> 09:36.259
♪ ♪

09:38.012 --> 09:39.463
I need you to find out
everything you can

09:39.597 --> 09:40.597
on Garrett Brady.

09:40.682 --> 09:42.466
Absolutely.
Who's Garrett Brady?

09:42.600 --> 09:44.280
The guy on the other side
of Gerard's suit.

09:46.304 --> 09:47.304
Wait a second.

09:47.305 --> 09:48.305
Does this mean
you took his case?

09:48.439 --> 09:50.223
You know that means
I took his case,

09:50.308 --> 09:51.358
and I don't want to hear
any gloating.

09:51.476 --> 09:52.642
Gloating?
No, no, no, no, no.

09:52.810 --> 09:53.894
I'm not--
I'm not gloating.

09:54.028 --> 09:55.729
I'm merely recognizing
the fact that you

09:55.863 --> 09:57.064
completely changed
your mind

09:57.198 --> 09:59.232
based entirely
on what I said.

09:59.367 --> 10:01.118
- Which is gloating.
- "Po-tay-to," "po-tah-to."

10:01.235 --> 10:02.819
But as long as you're
gonna think of it that way,

10:02.987 --> 10:04.121
I might as well point out

10:04.238 --> 10:05.956
that since you listened
to my lecture,

10:06.074 --> 10:08.125
maybe you should start
calling me Professor.

10:08.209 --> 10:09.876
I'm gonna start
calling you unemployed

10:09.994 --> 10:12.829
if you don't figure out a way
around using Gerard's alibi.

10:12.914 --> 10:14.965
Wait, we can't say where
the money came from?

10:15.049 --> 10:17.667
No, we can't, because
he was playing backroom poker,

10:17.752 --> 10:19.052
and if that comes out,
Harvard fires him.

10:19.170 --> 10:20.554
Are you kidding me?

10:20.671 --> 10:23.006
He's an ethics professor,
and he's breaking the law?

10:23.091 --> 10:25.058
Where the hell do you think
my chip comes from?

10:25.176 --> 10:26.309
[sighs]

10:26.427 --> 10:27.667
Well, if we can't use
his alibi,

10:27.678 --> 10:28.979
how are we supposed
to get him out of this?

10:29.063 --> 10:30.597
I don't know, Professor,
but you're the one

10:30.681 --> 10:31.921
who wanted us
to take this case,

10:31.983 --> 10:33.433
so why don't you use
that big brain of yours

10:33.518 --> 10:35.102
and find a solution?

10:38.573 --> 10:40.053
(Louis)
You're giving me Henry Gerard.

10:40.158 --> 10:41.158
(Harvey)
What?

10:41.159 --> 10:42.319
(Louis)
I saw him. I want him.

10:42.326 --> 10:43.360
You got him.
He's mine.

10:43.528 --> 10:44.578
That's not the way
it works, Louis.

10:44.695 --> 10:45.862
I'm afraid you'll have
to find yourself

10:45.997 --> 10:46.997
another boyfriend.

10:47.031 --> 10:49.916
Oh, this is exactly
how it works.

10:50.034 --> 10:51.585
You talked to Jessica,
didn't you?

10:51.702 --> 10:53.382
Sure did, and she used me
to cover her ass,

10:53.454 --> 10:55.172
so I get one
of your clients in return.

10:55.256 --> 10:57.290
You want one of my clients,
we can talk about that,

10:57.375 --> 10:58.759
but Gerard's
staying with me.

10:58.876 --> 11:00.210
Oh, please,
don't pretend

11:00.378 --> 11:01.658
like you actually care
about him.

11:01.712 --> 11:03.013
He can't even stand you.

11:03.097 --> 11:05.182
Louis, I just offered
to consider giving you

11:05.266 --> 11:06.266
one of my clients,

11:06.300 --> 11:08.101
so I suggest
you let Gerard go.

11:08.219 --> 11:09.459
No, I'm not letting
anything go,

11:09.554 --> 11:11.138
because it doesn't make
any sense.

11:11.222 --> 11:12.606
Not only can't he stand you.

11:12.723 --> 11:14.608
He doesn't respect you
because he's got things--

11:14.725 --> 11:16.109
What did you
just say to me?

11:16.227 --> 11:18.061
I said he doesn't
respect you.

11:18.146 --> 11:19.146
Well, you know what?

11:19.197 --> 11:21.148
He definitely
doesn't respect you,

11:21.232 --> 11:23.567
because when he told me
he needed a lawyer,

11:23.701 --> 11:25.535
I tried to send him
your way,

11:25.620 --> 11:27.204
and his exact words were,

11:27.288 --> 11:29.739
"I don't want Louis.
I want you."

11:32.627 --> 11:33.743
Fine.

11:33.911 --> 11:35.245
Then I'll just take
another one of your clients.

11:35.413 --> 11:37.547
- You're not taking a thing.
- You just said that I could--

11:37.632 --> 11:39.552
Look, I don't give a shit
what I just said, okay?

11:39.634 --> 11:41.051
My clients are my clients.

11:41.135 --> 11:42.169
And you don't get
out of my office

11:42.253 --> 11:43.420
in the next three seconds,

11:43.554 --> 11:45.088
something's gonna happen
between you and me,

11:45.223 --> 11:47.257
and I guarantee
it won't end with you

11:47.391 --> 11:49.843
keeping all of your teeth.

11:55.483 --> 11:56.600
No.

11:56.734 --> 11:58.401
Just turn around and walk
right back out that door.

11:58.519 --> 11:59.603
- Harvey.
- Did you hear what I said?

11:59.770 --> 12:00.987
I did, but apparently,
you didn't hear

12:01.105 --> 12:02.989
what Jessica said
about wiping the slate clean.

12:03.107 --> 12:04.608
And apparently, you didn't
hear what I said,

12:04.742 --> 12:06.827
because I just told Louis
he could have one of my clients.

12:06.944 --> 12:08.528
And three seconds later,
you told him he couldn't.

12:08.613 --> 12:09.946
Yeah, because I realized
that I'm paying

12:10.081 --> 12:11.198
for Jessica's mistake.

12:11.282 --> 12:13.283
No, Harvey, you were willing
to pay for her mistake

12:13.451 --> 12:15.585
right up until Louis said
Gerard doesn't respect you.

12:15.670 --> 12:17.030
Oh, that has nothing
to do with it.

12:17.038 --> 12:18.588
You can lie to yourself
all you want,

12:18.706 --> 12:19.873
but I'm not gonna
let you bullshit me.

12:19.957 --> 12:21.124
What the hell
are you talking about?

12:21.292 --> 12:23.043
Henry Gerard is the one
person you respect

12:23.127 --> 12:25.295
who never respected you,
and Louis touched that nerve.

12:25.429 --> 12:27.764
And I told you that
has nothing to do with it.

12:27.882 --> 12:28.882
You really think that?

12:28.966 --> 12:30.046
I don't think it.
I know it.

12:30.051 --> 12:31.091
Then you know what,
Harvey?

12:31.185 --> 12:32.385
You're no different
than Louis,

12:32.470 --> 12:34.390
because you have a chance
to help us all move on,

12:34.522 --> 12:36.242
and you are blowing it off
out of pettiness,

12:36.274 --> 12:37.858
which is exactly
what Louis would do.

12:37.975 --> 12:38.859
What do you want
from me, Donna?

12:38.976 --> 12:40.227
I want you
to be a grown-up

12:40.361 --> 12:42.979
and do what you said you'd do
in the first place.

12:49.581 --> 12:50.781
(Harvey)
You got something?

12:50.865 --> 12:52.647
(Mike) Yeah, we've been
overlooking the obvious.

12:52.648 --> 12:54.228
Yeah, I'm not in the mood
for 20 questions.

12:54.229 --> 12:55.229
Give it to me.

12:55.313 --> 12:56.647
Unless you're traveling
internationally

12:56.732 --> 12:58.432
and don't report it,
carrying cash on board a plane

12:58.517 --> 12:59.517
isn't a crime.

12:59.601 --> 13:00.818
Great,
except for the fact

13:00.936 --> 13:02.436
that Gerard's not being
charged with smuggling.

13:02.521 --> 13:03.521
He's being sued.

13:03.522 --> 13:04.522
Right, but my point is,

13:04.573 --> 13:06.173
how did Garrett Brady
even find that out?

13:06.274 --> 13:08.192
Well, he found out
because Gerard

13:08.326 --> 13:09.493
was detained by the TSA.

13:09.578 --> 13:11.112
Who talked to him
for five minutes

13:11.196 --> 13:12.446
and then sent him
on his way.

13:12.581 --> 13:13.864
Those searches
aren't a matter

13:13.999 --> 13:14.999
of public record.

13:15.083 --> 13:16.500
- Exactly.
- Holy shit.

13:16.618 --> 13:17.618
Brady bribed the TSA.

13:17.703 --> 13:18.703
Which isn't only illegal.

13:18.754 --> 13:20.871
It makes that report
totally inadmissible.

13:20.956 --> 13:22.289
You figured this out
on your own?

13:22.374 --> 13:24.175
Well, I would've done it faster,
but I had to order some sushi.

13:24.292 --> 13:26.377
[chuckles]
"Would've done it faster."

13:26.478 --> 13:27.712
That's what you said
your first week here,

13:27.846 --> 13:29.430
except it was pizza
instead of sushi.

13:29.548 --> 13:30.548
Yeah, I'm growing.

13:30.716 --> 13:32.883
You mean Rachel
taught you how to eat.

13:33.018 --> 13:34.769
Like I said,
I'm growing.

13:37.806 --> 13:40.224
Hey, Donna, I'm a little
busy at the moment.

13:40.358 --> 13:42.059
Too busy to take on this?

13:42.194 --> 13:43.194
What's that?

13:43.278 --> 13:44.729
Just the first client
that Jessica gave Harvey

13:44.863 --> 13:46.230
when he made name partner.

13:46.364 --> 13:47.898
Harvey said he wouldn't
let me have any of his clients.

13:48.033 --> 13:49.366
No.
He said he would.

13:49.451 --> 13:51.011
But then instead
of taking him up on it,

13:51.036 --> 13:52.319
you went ahead
and shit on his feelings.

13:52.454 --> 13:53.738
Please.
Harvey doesn't have feelings.

13:53.872 --> 13:55.372
That's not true,
and you know it.

13:55.457 --> 13:56.741
And you of all people
should know that a person

13:56.875 --> 13:58.209
can overreact
when they're hurt.

13:58.326 --> 13:59.376
If you're referring to me,

13:59.494 --> 14:00.578
I do not overreact when--

14:00.662 --> 14:02.246
Okay, whatever you say,
Fatty-Baldy.

14:02.414 --> 14:05.549
Okay, get the hell
out of my office and--

14:05.667 --> 14:08.219
Fine, you have a small,
legitimate point.

14:08.336 --> 14:09.253
I really hurt his feelings?

14:09.387 --> 14:10.671
Yeah, you really did.

14:10.756 --> 14:12.316
But then he realized
he was overreacting

14:12.390 --> 14:13.674
and that this was
a chance for us all

14:13.759 --> 14:15.392
to get back
to where we were.

14:15.510 --> 14:16.927
You swear that is
the first client

14:17.095 --> 14:19.096
that Jessica gave him
after me made name partner?

14:19.181 --> 14:21.065
I swear.

14:21.183 --> 14:23.067
Leave me the file.

14:36.281 --> 14:38.415
You two go ahead.
I haven't decided yet.

14:38.500 --> 14:39.834
Actually, we're not here
for the falafel.

14:39.951 --> 14:41.535
We're here to introduce
ourselves.

14:41.670 --> 14:42.670
Mike Ross.

14:42.671 --> 14:43.537
Harvey Specter.

14:43.622 --> 14:45.005
We represent
Henry Gerard.

14:45.123 --> 14:46.373
Ah.
[laughs]

14:46.508 --> 14:48.292
Well, in that case,
let me buy you two lunch,

14:48.426 --> 14:50.594
because I'm about to come
into an unexpected windfall.

14:50.679 --> 14:51.959
Well, I guess
that's your thing--

14:52.047 --> 14:53.297
paying people off.

14:53.431 --> 14:55.549
I hope the TSA got more
than some shitty falafel.

14:55.634 --> 14:56.934
What the hell
are you talking about?

14:57.018 --> 14:58.435
I'm talking about this.

15:01.556 --> 15:03.474
Oh. Bribery?

15:03.608 --> 15:04.809
(Harvey)
Ironic, isn't it?

15:04.943 --> 15:07.561
You suing Professor Gerard
for accepting a bribe

15:07.696 --> 15:09.697
when you're the one
paying off federal employees.

15:09.815 --> 15:11.148
Allegedly paying,
Counselor.

15:11.283 --> 15:12.283
Tsk, tsk, tsk.

15:12.317 --> 15:13.651
You don't want
to slander me.

15:13.785 --> 15:15.536
- So you admit it.
- I don't admit a thing.

15:15.654 --> 15:17.321
Your client sold out victims
of a train derailment.

15:17.455 --> 15:18.539
He's going to pay.

15:18.657 --> 15:20.457
You may not be willing
to admit anything here,

15:20.575 --> 15:22.076
but you'll have to
in front of the judge.

15:22.160 --> 15:23.160
Because I've drafted
subpoenas

15:23.245 --> 15:25.830
for every TSA employee
on duty that night.

15:25.964 --> 15:27.915
Drop the case,
Mr. Brady.

15:27.999 --> 15:29.083
Are you threatening me?

15:29.167 --> 15:31.085
No, we're informing you.

15:31.169 --> 15:32.670
Well, let me inform you.

15:32.838 --> 15:34.138
In case you forgot,
the TSA falls

15:34.256 --> 15:35.896
under the Department
of Homeland Security,

15:36.007 --> 15:37.474
which makes this
a national security issue.

15:37.592 --> 15:38.592
This has nothing to do

15:38.643 --> 15:40.511
with national security,
and you know it.

15:40.595 --> 15:41.979
All I know is
the government found

15:42.097 --> 15:43.264
a large sum of cash
on a passenger.

15:43.398 --> 15:44.348
Now, how they came
to know that,

15:44.516 --> 15:45.683
how they proceeded
to investigate that,

15:45.817 --> 15:46.934
or what they did
with that information

15:47.068 --> 15:48.228
is the government's business.

15:48.270 --> 15:49.320
And that's what
you're going with?

15:49.404 --> 15:50.437
That's not what
I'm going with.

15:50.522 --> 15:52.356
That's what they're
going to go with.

15:52.490 --> 15:55.359
So you can call up as many
TSA agents as you like,

15:55.443 --> 15:56.777
but they're not gonna be
saying a thing.

15:56.862 --> 15:59.697
And you can buy
your own damn falafel.

16:06.838 --> 16:07.838
[snaps fingers]

16:07.839 --> 16:08.923
I need
Cutie Pie Cosmetics.

16:09.040 --> 16:10.291
You want to try
that again?

16:10.375 --> 16:11.592
I have a meeting
with Joan Walsh tonight,

16:11.710 --> 16:12.877
and I need her files.

16:12.961 --> 16:13.961
Joan is Harvey's client.

16:14.095 --> 16:15.596
- Not anymore.
- Since when?

16:15.714 --> 16:17.181
Since it doesn't matter,

16:17.299 --> 16:18.632
because I'm name partner,

16:18.767 --> 16:21.101
which means when I say
I need something,

16:21.219 --> 16:22.186
your response
should either be,

16:22.304 --> 16:24.271
"How high?"
or "Can I have another?"

16:26.024 --> 16:27.024
Fine.

16:27.058 --> 16:28.359
There are a few things
that you should know--

16:28.443 --> 16:29.894
You see,
what I know is

16:29.978 --> 16:31.228
your boss seems to think

16:31.363 --> 16:32.980
all it takes
to impress Joan Walsh

16:33.064 --> 16:35.566
is getting Donna to make
a fancy dinner reservation,

16:35.700 --> 16:38.035
but I'm going to impress her
with so much legal domination

16:38.153 --> 16:39.313
that by the end of the night,

16:39.404 --> 16:40.404
all she's gonna be able
to say is,

16:40.538 --> 16:42.206
"Harvey Specter who?"

16:42.324 --> 16:43.574
- Okay, that's a mistake--
- A mistake?

16:43.742 --> 16:44.742
Oh, I get it.

16:44.826 --> 16:45.993
You're trying to impress me

16:46.127 --> 16:47.411
with your legal domination

16:47.495 --> 16:49.496
to prove that you're not
just a paralegal

16:49.631 --> 16:50.631
but an associate.

16:50.665 --> 16:51.799
No, Louis. I'm--

16:51.917 --> 16:53.384
See, I don't care
what you call yourself.

16:53.501 --> 16:55.419
So unless you did
such a shitty job,

16:55.553 --> 16:56.887
the files are unreadable,

16:57.005 --> 16:58.806
hand 'em over to me
right now.

17:21.613 --> 17:23.414
That's more like it.

17:38.964 --> 17:40.014
What's this?

17:40.131 --> 17:41.265
I know you have
to work tonight,

17:41.349 --> 17:42.633
but you also need to eat.

17:42.717 --> 17:44.134
I wouldn't call this
just eating.

17:44.219 --> 17:46.053
Well, you deserve better
than paper plates.

17:46.187 --> 17:47.888
I don't mind paper plates.

17:48.023 --> 17:49.807
Oh, I know you don't.

17:49.941 --> 17:51.358
I just said
you deserve better.

17:51.476 --> 17:53.143
Is that <i> ropa vieja?</i>

17:53.278 --> 17:54.361
Hmm.

17:54.479 --> 17:56.280
I made it myself.

17:56.398 --> 17:58.065
Which means you got it
at the Cuban place

17:58.199 --> 18:00.617
that I love
on 40th and Lex.

18:00.702 --> 18:01.735
By myself.

18:01.870 --> 18:04.154
What did I do
to deserve this?

18:04.289 --> 18:06.824
I don't know.

18:06.908 --> 18:09.043
I'm just...

18:09.160 --> 18:11.328
feeling closer.

18:11.463 --> 18:12.663
Because I confided
in you.

18:12.797 --> 18:14.331
Because the walls
are coming down,

18:14.416 --> 18:16.333
and I can feel it.

18:19.471 --> 18:21.972
What did I do
to deserve you?

18:22.057 --> 18:23.557
Mm, well, we can
talk about that

18:23.675 --> 18:28.312
over this delicious meal
that I made all by myself.

18:28.430 --> 18:31.315
[gentle piano music]

18:31.433 --> 18:38.522
♪ ♪

18:38.656 --> 18:39.656
To us.

18:39.657 --> 18:42.526
[glasses clink]

18:42.610 --> 18:44.244
[laughs]

18:44.362 --> 18:46.363
And then I said,
"Helen,

18:46.498 --> 18:47.998
"that's no Pomeranian.

18:48.083 --> 18:49.666
"That's a Pomimo.

18:49.784 --> 18:51.668
- You've been had."
- [laughing]

18:51.786 --> 18:54.872
Oh-ho-ho,
that is hilarious.

18:55.006 --> 18:56.540
Really, dogs,
they are--

18:56.624 --> 18:58.008
they are so fascinating.

18:58.093 --> 18:59.376
Do you have many dogs,
Louis?

18:59.544 --> 19:00.544
Hell, no.

19:02.797 --> 19:05.682
Building regulations--
it's a clusterf-f-f...

19:05.800 --> 19:07.301
I've been fighting them
for years.

19:07.435 --> 19:08.886
- Oh, that's horrible.
- Yes.

19:09.054 --> 19:11.055
As is what's going on
with your stock.

19:11.139 --> 19:12.139
Oh, Louis,
we're having dinner.

19:12.223 --> 19:13.440
- Put that away.
- No, no, no.

19:13.558 --> 19:14.808
But I just thought you'd
be interested to know

19:14.943 --> 19:16.026
that we could skyrocket
the share price--

19:16.111 --> 19:17.694
Right now
what I'm interested in

19:17.779 --> 19:18.896
is having another Manhattan

19:18.980 --> 19:20.500
and hearing what's
on the dessert list.

19:20.532 --> 19:21.865
Oh, you don't need a list.
Get the crème brûlée.

19:21.983 --> 19:22.900
Now, this stock issue,
I have--

19:23.034 --> 19:24.401
Fax the papers to my office,

19:24.486 --> 19:25.926
and I'll review them
when I get home.

19:25.954 --> 19:26.954
When you get home?

19:26.988 --> 19:28.906
What the f-f...

19:29.074 --> 19:30.874
What the hell did we come
to dinner for, then?

19:30.959 --> 19:31.992
For this.

19:32.127 --> 19:33.127
What this?

19:33.128 --> 19:34.795
This.

19:36.464 --> 19:37.915
Okay.

19:38.049 --> 19:40.217
I don't know how Harvey handled
these quarterly reviews, but I--

19:40.301 --> 19:41.552
Oh, Harvey...

19:41.636 --> 19:43.003
was magnificent.

19:43.088 --> 19:44.555
[sighs]

19:44.639 --> 19:46.279
Truth be told,
I was a little disappointed

19:46.307 --> 19:47.867
when I heard that
you'd be handling this

19:47.892 --> 19:48.892
instead of him,

19:48.927 --> 19:50.594
but I haven't seen
your cha-cha yet,

19:50.728 --> 19:51.895
so the jury's still out.

19:52.013 --> 19:54.181
- That was a lawyer joke.
- Yep. Got it.

19:54.315 --> 19:55.432
- [laughs]
- Yep.

19:55.567 --> 19:57.768
Listen, Joan,

19:57.902 --> 19:59.603
I think you're
gonna be really glad

19:59.737 --> 20:01.021
that it was me here
tonight,

20:01.156 --> 20:03.073
because I already sent
a letter to your board.

20:03.158 --> 20:04.491
- You did what?
- And I--

20:04.609 --> 20:06.326
I notified them of this.

20:06.444 --> 20:07.444
That's what--

20:07.495 --> 20:09.279
what I'm trying
to tell you.

20:13.918 --> 20:15.285
Why the hell
would you do something

20:15.420 --> 20:16.870
so patently stupid?

20:17.005 --> 20:18.338
Stupid?

20:18.456 --> 20:20.707
Hey, I didn't become
name partner being stupid.

20:20.792 --> 20:21.792
Didn't you?

20:21.793 --> 20:22.793
Two members of my board

20:22.794 --> 20:24.595
are about to reach
their term limits.

20:24.679 --> 20:26.679
At least one is being circled
by Glamour Cosmetics.

20:26.764 --> 20:29.550
You have just notified
that person of a product

20:29.634 --> 20:31.518
that I've had in R & D
for years,

20:31.636 --> 20:33.971
and now they can trade
information

20:34.105 --> 20:37.224
for a seat on the board
of my biggest competitor.

20:37.358 --> 20:38.392
Joan, I didn't know--

20:38.476 --> 20:40.527
Tell me, Mr. Litt,

20:40.645 --> 20:43.397
did you actually graduate
from law school,

20:43.481 --> 20:46.150
or did you just buy your way
onto the letterhead?

21:00.282 --> 21:02.333
[sighs]

21:06.171 --> 21:07.794
Yeah, you better put
that bag down,

21:07.795 --> 21:09.096
because we're staying
all night.

21:11.746 --> 21:13.026
Didn't go well with Joan,
did it?

21:13.031 --> 21:14.698
No, it didn't, because
you sandbagged me.

21:14.782 --> 21:15.949
I didn't sandbag you.

21:16.084 --> 21:17.284
Well, then what do you call
not telling me

21:17.418 --> 21:18.752
that Glamour was circling
her board members?

21:18.870 --> 21:20.037
I tried to tell you,

21:20.121 --> 21:21.588
but you couldn't hear me
through all of your rage.

21:21.706 --> 21:22.756
What I'm not hearing

21:22.874 --> 21:24.625
is the sound of you
putting your bag down,

21:24.759 --> 21:26.627
because the board members
are meeting tomorrow afternoon,

21:26.761 --> 21:28.812
and I only have until then
to fix this.

21:28.913 --> 21:30.097
And you want me
to help you?

21:30.214 --> 21:31.632
You're the associate
on this case, aren't you?

21:31.766 --> 21:33.646
- So now I'm an associate?
- Hey, you know what?

21:33.768 --> 21:34.718
Now is not the time
to get into it.

21:34.802 --> 21:36.303
No, now is exactly the time
to get into it,

21:36.387 --> 21:39.389
because you have taken
every opportunity possible

21:39.524 --> 21:41.274
to make me feel like
I am nothing,

21:41.392 --> 21:43.310
and now, even though
you want something,

21:43.394 --> 21:45.034
you're still treating me
like I'm nothing.

21:45.146 --> 21:46.697
I'm treating you like
every other associate.

21:46.781 --> 21:47.731
That is bullshit,
and you know what?

21:47.865 --> 21:48.865
Even if it were true,

21:48.900 --> 21:50.484
you didn't used to
treat me that way.

21:52.236 --> 21:55.322
I didn't used to know you
lied to me on a daily basis.

21:55.406 --> 21:58.625
Louis, it would serve
you right

21:58.743 --> 22:01.962
if I take my bag
and leave you here

22:02.080 --> 22:03.964
and go home to the man
that I love.

22:04.082 --> 22:05.082
So you're not gonna help.

22:05.216 --> 22:06.717
No, I'm gonna help you,

22:06.801 --> 22:08.669
but not because
you deserve it.

22:08.753 --> 22:11.004
I'll do it because I am
an associate,

22:11.089 --> 22:14.591
and I am a professional,
which means I am capable

22:14.676 --> 22:17.594
of putting the personal aside
in order to do my job.

22:22.600 --> 22:23.567
(Mike)
And one of those, please.

22:23.685 --> 22:25.485
Just what I was
in the mood for.

22:25.603 --> 22:26.683
Ah, you're getting a bagel.

22:26.771 --> 22:27.904
That means you kicked ass.

22:27.989 --> 22:29.823
Which I did.

22:29.941 --> 22:31.024
You called up the TSA,

22:31.159 --> 22:32.826
busted up their
national security defense?

22:32.944 --> 22:34.578
No, I used their defense.

22:34.662 --> 22:36.079
Gerard's gonna testify
under seal

22:36.164 --> 22:38.115
because it's a matter
of national security.

22:38.249 --> 22:39.332
And the judge
bought that?

22:39.450 --> 22:40.450
What's not to buy?

22:40.501 --> 22:41.918
The TSA made
the argument for us.

22:42.036 --> 22:42.919
And what did Brady say?

22:43.004 --> 22:45.122
That's the best part
about it.

22:45.206 --> 22:46.957
He doesn't even know it.

22:47.091 --> 22:49.126
It's a matter
of national security.

22:49.210 --> 22:50.427
We testify under seal,

22:50.511 --> 22:53.180
the judge realizes that Gerard
is a degenerate gambler...

22:53.297 --> 22:54.297
But a fair mediator.

22:54.298 --> 22:56.099
The case gets dismissed,
and Garrett Brady

22:56.184 --> 22:58.135
and Harvard Law
never know it happened.

22:58.269 --> 22:59.789
You thought of all
of that on your own?

22:59.854 --> 23:01.354
You think you're the only
one who can come up

23:01.472 --> 23:03.106
with an intelligent solution?

23:03.224 --> 23:04.307
You are 1 for 400

23:04.442 --> 23:05.892
in the time
we've worked together.

23:05.977 --> 23:08.228
Okay, smart guy, since
I did your job for you,

23:08.312 --> 23:09.896
you're gonna do
my job for me.

23:10.031 --> 23:11.148
You want me to prep Gerard

23:11.282 --> 23:12.282
because you don't
want to sit in a room

23:12.400 --> 23:13.734
and listen to him talk
for two hours.

23:13.818 --> 23:15.402
I didn't want to
15 years ago,

23:15.486 --> 23:16.703
and I don't want to now.

23:16.821 --> 23:18.905
We only get
one shot at this,

23:18.990 --> 23:21.074
and his testimony
better be rock solid.

23:21.159 --> 23:22.159
Thanks.

23:22.293 --> 23:25.378
Oh, yeah, sure,
help yourself!

23:25.496 --> 23:26.713
Dick.

23:33.337 --> 23:35.172
I see you haven't slept.

23:35.306 --> 23:36.807
I have a lot of work
that needs attending to.

23:36.924 --> 23:38.892
I bet you do, considering
the phone call

23:39.010 --> 23:40.370
I got from Joan Walsh
this morning.

23:40.394 --> 23:42.095
[groans]
She called you?

23:42.230 --> 23:44.070
She wanted to know what
the other name partners

23:44.148 --> 23:46.433
were going to do about the one
that screwed the pooch.

23:46.517 --> 23:47.768
Oh, come on,
that is not fair.

23:47.852 --> 23:48.935
I didn't have all
the information--

23:49.070 --> 23:50.487
You had enough information

23:50.605 --> 23:52.155
to make a deal
to get her from Harvey,

23:52.273 --> 23:53.990
and part of that deal was
you backing me with Jeff.

23:54.075 --> 23:55.242
Oh, so that's why
you're here.

23:55.359 --> 23:56.493
You don't trust
I'm still gonna do it?

23:56.611 --> 23:57.944
Because you haven't
done it yet,

23:58.079 --> 23:59.919
and you have a history
of making poor decisions

24:00.031 --> 24:01.364
when things aren't
going your way.

24:01.499 --> 24:02.916
The only poor decision
I've made is agreeing

24:03.034 --> 24:04.167
to cover for you
in the first place.

24:04.285 --> 24:05.502
You didn't think that
was such a bad idea

24:05.620 --> 24:07.037
when you were using it
to get what you wanted.

24:07.121 --> 24:08.705
And now you're threatening
to take that thing away.

24:08.873 --> 24:10.457
Louis, you want
to keep Joan,

24:10.591 --> 24:11.591
that's on you,

24:11.626 --> 24:13.927
but I held up my end
of the bargain.

24:14.045 --> 24:15.545
You better hold up yours.

24:21.219 --> 24:23.637
(Mike) I just want to go over it
one more time, Professor.

24:23.771 --> 24:25.138
How much money
was in that pot?

24:25.223 --> 24:27.858
I'm tried
of going over it.

24:27.942 --> 24:29.559
Why do we have
to keep replaying

24:29.644 --> 24:31.027
every moment of this game?

24:31.112 --> 24:32.979
Because your entire case
depends on it.

24:33.064 --> 24:36.233
My case depends on the fact
that I won that money gambling,

24:36.317 --> 24:38.068
not whether I won it
with a flush.

24:38.202 --> 24:40.120
Your case depends on
the judge believing you,

24:40.238 --> 24:42.205
and if he finds any holes
in your testimony, then we--

24:42.290 --> 24:44.741
I gave you the names of
everyone I knew at that game.

24:44.876 --> 24:47.116
But none of those men were
there when you won that money.

24:47.211 --> 24:49.796
I can't help it if I didn't
get the name of the guy I beat.

24:49.914 --> 24:52.799
Which is why your story
needs to be rock solid.

24:56.387 --> 24:58.088
Okay.

24:58.222 --> 24:59.756
Go ahead.

24:59.891 --> 25:01.508
So I ask you again,
Professor,

25:01.642 --> 25:03.260
how much money
was in the final pot?

25:03.344 --> 25:05.178
Roughly $12,000.

25:05.313 --> 25:06.313
And you won that hand.

25:06.430 --> 25:07.931
As I said before,
I won,

25:08.015 --> 25:09.015
and then I cashed out.

25:09.100 --> 25:10.180
And what did you
have again?

25:10.184 --> 25:11.184
A queen-high flush.

25:11.235 --> 25:12.569
And who did you beat?

25:12.653 --> 25:14.104
I told you,
I didn't get his name.

25:14.272 --> 25:15.438
Okay, so what
did he have?

25:15.573 --> 25:18.358
Two pair,
queens over sixes.

25:21.913 --> 25:22.913
Wait a second.

25:22.947 --> 25:25.282
You said before that
the man next to you

25:25.416 --> 25:26.533
folded with two queens up,

25:26.617 --> 25:27.857
and now this guy
has two queens,

25:27.919 --> 25:28.919
and you had
a queen-high flush?

25:29.003 --> 25:31.338
I said that the man
next to me

25:31.455 --> 25:32.455
folded with two kings.

25:32.590 --> 25:33.456
No, you didn't.

25:33.541 --> 25:34.591
You heard me wrong.

25:34.709 --> 25:36.426
No, I didn't.

25:36.510 --> 25:37.961
Is this part
of prepping me,

25:38.045 --> 25:39.462
or are you accusing me
of something?

25:39.597 --> 25:40.797
I'm trying to get
your story to line up.

25:40.932 --> 25:43.216
- My story does line up.
- Not to me, it doesn't.

25:43.301 --> 25:44.935
Look, young man, if you're
gonna sit over there

25:45.019 --> 25:46.019
and call me a liar--

25:46.103 --> 25:47.187
I'm not calling you a liar,

25:47.305 --> 25:49.025
but if you say tomorrow
what you said today,

25:49.140 --> 25:50.140
we're gonna be
in a lot of trouble,

25:50.308 --> 25:51.348
because where I come from,

25:51.392 --> 25:52.943
there are only
four queens in a deck.

25:53.027 --> 25:54.861
I said two kings,

25:54.979 --> 25:57.480
and I'm gonna say that
again tomorrow.

25:57.565 --> 26:00.367
So you do your job,

26:00.484 --> 26:02.035
and I'm gonna do mine.

26:08.826 --> 26:09.826
(Mike)
He's lying.

26:09.911 --> 26:11.044
What are you talking about?

26:11.162 --> 26:12.412
Gerard's story about
winning all that money

26:12.546 --> 26:13.630
playing poker is bullshit.

26:13.714 --> 26:15.498
All right, slow down.
What the hell happened?

26:15.633 --> 26:17.334
I did the math,
and the hands don't add up.

26:17.418 --> 26:18.738
What do you mean
you did the math?

26:18.836 --> 26:20.670
I mean first he said that he
drew a queen on fourth street,

26:20.805 --> 26:22.055
and then when I pressed
him about it, he--

26:22.173 --> 26:23.223
Wait a second.

26:23.341 --> 26:24.925
This conclusion is based
on him recalling hands

26:25.009 --> 26:26.343
under cross-examination?

26:26.427 --> 26:27.427
Harvey, I got kicked out

26:27.511 --> 26:28.911
of Atlantic City
for counting cards.

26:29.013 --> 26:30.397
- I know this shit.
- It doesn't mean he's lying.

26:30.514 --> 26:31.982
I got a little experience
with that too,

26:32.066 --> 26:33.483
and I'm telling you,
he was.

26:33.601 --> 26:35.735
- Or maybe he's tired.
- Or maybe I'm right.

26:35.853 --> 26:37.737
Or maybe you don't know what
the hell you're talking about.

26:37.855 --> 26:40.440
- Why are you defending him?
- Because you asked me to.

26:45.279 --> 26:47.414
Look, Harvey,

26:47.531 --> 26:49.115
I'm not saying that
he took a bribe.

26:49.250 --> 26:52.953
I'm just saying that he didn't
get that money playing poker.

26:53.037 --> 26:56.256
Well, unless he admitted that,
he's testifying tomorrow.

26:57.875 --> 27:01.378
Since when do you stick
your head in the sand?

27:01.545 --> 27:03.513
- Did he admit it?
- No, he didn't.

27:03.631 --> 27:05.711
But he screwed up the details,
and he shouldn't have,

27:05.800 --> 27:08.601
because people who are telling
the truth get it right.

27:08.719 --> 27:10.887
And you know it.

27:25.641 --> 27:26.641
What's that?

27:26.675 --> 27:28.009
Jacks full of fours.

27:28.144 --> 27:29.811
I can see that,
but why--

27:29.929 --> 27:31.563
Why is it staring you
in the face?

27:31.647 --> 27:34.265
It's what I threw down
the last time I won a huge hand.

27:34.350 --> 27:38.570
It was six weeks ago,
and I can remember every hand

27:38.654 --> 27:40.355
that every player
at that table had.

27:40.439 --> 27:41.919
Now, if you won money
the other night,

27:41.991 --> 27:43.024
you'd remember it too.

27:43.159 --> 27:44.275
I do remember,

27:44.443 --> 27:45.944
and as I explained
to your associate--

27:46.078 --> 27:48.496
Yeah, stop bullshitting me.

27:48.614 --> 27:50.882
Where the hell did that
money really come from?

27:51.000 --> 27:52.083
'Cause if you don't
tell me the truth,

27:52.201 --> 27:53.641
I'm canceling
that hearing right now.

27:56.372 --> 27:58.590
It came...

27:58.674 --> 28:00.458
from a student of mine.

28:00.593 --> 28:01.759
For what?

28:01.861 --> 28:04.295
In exchange
for changing his grade.

28:04.430 --> 28:06.798
Jesus Christ.
For $25,000?

28:06.932 --> 28:08.633
He was going to fail
my class,

28:08.717 --> 28:10.468
and that would've stopped him
from getting an offer from--

28:10.603 --> 28:12.137
You goddamn hypocrite.

28:12.221 --> 28:14.639
You preach about ethics,
and you do this?

28:14.807 --> 28:16.691
This is about ethics.

28:16.809 --> 28:18.643
And you don't have
any idea why I did it.

28:18.777 --> 28:20.645
I don't care
why you did it.

28:20.779 --> 28:22.397
I care about what
you're making me do,

28:22.481 --> 28:24.032
because I am not
suborning perjury.

28:24.150 --> 28:27.068
Well, you tell me that you've
never done anything worse.

28:28.988 --> 28:31.039
I knew it.

28:31.157 --> 28:33.741
You would do it
for someone else...

28:33.826 --> 28:35.126
but not for me.

28:35.244 --> 28:37.245
You know what, Professor?

28:37.329 --> 28:39.380
There's a small part of me
that actually thought

28:39.498 --> 28:41.833
that you came to me because
you thought I'm the best,

28:41.917 --> 28:44.085
but you just think I'll do
whatever it takes to win.

28:44.220 --> 28:46.421
Isn't that what
makes you the best?

28:47.973 --> 28:49.493
Get someone else
to do your dirty work,

28:49.508 --> 28:51.392
because I'm not
suborning perjury.

28:54.730 --> 28:56.598
[Louis sighs]

28:56.732 --> 28:59.601
[grunting]

29:07.109 --> 29:08.193
What are you doing?

29:08.277 --> 29:09.277
[grunts]

29:09.411 --> 29:10.612
Getting my blood flowing.

29:10.746 --> 29:12.030
I've been sitting here
all night,

29:12.164 --> 29:14.999
and restless leg syndrome
kills 14 people every hour.

29:15.117 --> 29:16.277
I don't think
that's accurate.

29:16.335 --> 29:18.036
I don't care what you think.
What do you have?

29:18.120 --> 29:19.754
I found a way to fix
things with Joan.

29:19.872 --> 29:21.706
[grunts]

29:25.461 --> 29:26.941
Okay, you're arguing
anything in R & D

29:26.962 --> 29:28.082
is the intellectual property

29:28.130 --> 29:29.380
of the person
who suggested the product?

29:29.515 --> 29:31.599
Until such time that
the results become public.

29:31.717 --> 29:33.384
Which they did the second
I sent the board that letter.

29:33.469 --> 29:34.469
Except board members
are subject

29:34.553 --> 29:35.603
to the nondisclosure
agreement.

29:35.721 --> 29:36.888
Well, the board members
haven't signed

29:36.972 --> 29:37.889
a nondisclosure agreement.

29:37.973 --> 29:40.024
Yet.

29:40.109 --> 29:41.476
What's to stop them
from refusing?

29:41.560 --> 29:42.560
Nothing,
but if they do,

29:42.611 --> 29:43.778
then the noncompete
kicks in.

29:43.896 --> 29:45.730
Preventing them from revealing
the contents of my letter

29:45.814 --> 29:47.065
under threat of prosecution.

29:47.149 --> 29:48.866
Specifically
corporate espionage.

29:48.951 --> 29:50.902
Oh, my God.
You got this idea from--

29:51.036 --> 29:52.320
- Our bylaws.
- My bylaws.

29:52.404 --> 29:55.156
Rachel, holy shit,
this is...

29:55.241 --> 29:56.658
acceptable.

29:58.794 --> 30:00.912
I think the word you're
looking for is "awesome."

30:01.080 --> 30:03.298
Well, the word I'm saying
is, "Get out,

30:03.415 --> 30:04.632
because I have a meeting
to prepare for."

30:04.750 --> 30:06.884
You know what, Louis?
I have been working all night.

30:06.969 --> 30:09.220
And this gets your ass
out of a major sling,

30:09.305 --> 30:10.922
so instead of dismissing me,

30:11.006 --> 30:12.390
you should be asking me
to come with you.

30:12.508 --> 30:13.808
Excuse me,
Miss Professional.

30:13.926 --> 30:15.426
You wanted me to treat you
like every other associate.

30:15.594 --> 30:17.314
- Now I am.
- By acting as if I did nothing?

30:17.396 --> 30:19.430
No, by acknowledging
you did acceptable work.

30:19.515 --> 30:20.648
Letting you come with me
is something

30:20.766 --> 30:22.684
that I would only do for you
if we were friends,

30:22.818 --> 30:23.818
which we are not.

30:26.438 --> 30:29.107
[scoffs]

30:35.497 --> 30:38.082
You canceled the hearing.

30:38.200 --> 30:39.834
You were right.

30:39.952 --> 30:42.954
He was lying.

30:43.038 --> 30:45.340
I'm sorry.

30:45.457 --> 30:46.674
You know, I knew
he was a hypocrite

30:46.792 --> 30:48.259
after I found out
about the gambling.

30:48.377 --> 30:51.179
I never thought
he'd sell out Harvard.

30:53.515 --> 30:54.716
What are you
talking about?

30:54.850 --> 30:56.050
He did take the bribe,

30:56.135 --> 30:58.135
but it had nothing to do
with the accident victims.

30:58.187 --> 31:00.355
He did it to change
someone's grade.

31:02.524 --> 31:03.524
Why would he do that?

31:03.559 --> 31:04.692
What difference
does it make?

31:04.810 --> 31:06.861
Either way, he was gonna
let me suborn perjury.

31:06.979 --> 31:09.113
It makes a difference because
we still have to win this case.

31:09.231 --> 31:11.115
Oh, I don't give a shit
about winning this case.

31:11.200 --> 31:13.735
[scoffs]

31:13.819 --> 31:15.820
I've never heard you say
anything like that before.

31:15.954 --> 31:19.073
You--you care
about winning every case,

31:19.158 --> 31:20.198
every game,
every argument.

31:20.242 --> 31:21.242
Did you hear me?

31:21.377 --> 31:22.910
He was gonna let me
suborn perjury.

31:22.995 --> 31:24.629
And so would
every client you have

31:24.713 --> 31:25.963
if they thought
they'd get away with it.

31:26.081 --> 31:27.165
He's not every client.

31:27.299 --> 31:28.750
No, he's the one you hated
in the first place.

31:28.884 --> 31:30.585
- I didn't hate him.
- Harvey, what is going on here?

31:30.669 --> 31:34.505
I thought he was
better than us.

31:34.640 --> 31:36.641
I sat in that class
and listened to him talk

31:36.759 --> 31:39.811
about what kind
of lawyers we should be,

31:39.928 --> 31:42.347
and I always let him down
because I knew

31:42.481 --> 31:45.099
that wasn't the kind
of lawyer that wins.

31:45.184 --> 31:46.851
And I wanted to win.

31:46.985 --> 31:48.853
So I'd argue with him,

31:48.987 --> 31:51.072
and he'd look down on me.

31:52.908 --> 31:56.944
And now instead of you
letting him down,

31:57.029 --> 31:58.279
he let you down.

31:58.414 --> 32:01.332
He turned out to be
no better than any of us.

32:08.207 --> 32:11.759
So then let's make him
better than us.

32:15.631 --> 32:18.516
[indistinct chatter]

32:22.354 --> 32:23.388
Miss Walsh.

32:23.522 --> 32:25.273
(Walsh) You are not on my schedule
today.

32:25.391 --> 32:27.892
Ah, ah, Miss Walsh,
please take a look at this.

32:27.976 --> 32:29.060
What is it?

32:29.194 --> 32:30.278
It's a chance
to make things right.

32:30.396 --> 32:31.779
Ha.

32:33.399 --> 32:35.817
You cannot call
board members employees

32:35.951 --> 32:38.202
based on them having access
to an expense account.

32:38.287 --> 32:39.987
Not just an expense account.

32:40.072 --> 32:42.323
They have corporate cards
and standing offices,

32:42.408 --> 32:44.375
which, as defined
by section 14.2

32:44.460 --> 32:46.177
of the Internal Revenue Code,

32:46.278 --> 32:47.712
makes them employees.

32:47.830 --> 32:49.497
Well, Mr. Litt,

32:49.631 --> 32:52.550
seems I won't be demanding
a new point person after all.

32:52.668 --> 32:54.802
I'm glad to hear that.

32:54.920 --> 32:55.920
[scoffs]
Are you?

32:55.971 --> 32:57.004
Of course I am.

32:57.139 --> 32:58.673
You're my first client
as name partner.

32:58.807 --> 33:00.007
You're very important
to me.

33:01.677 --> 33:03.237
Well, I suppose
we'll find out the truth

33:03.262 --> 33:04.762
when someone else
makes name partner.

33:04.897 --> 33:06.264
What are you talking about?

33:06.398 --> 33:07.815
I'm not an idiot.

33:07.933 --> 33:09.901
I know that no one in your firm
wants to deal with me.

33:09.985 --> 33:10.985
That's not true.

33:11.103 --> 33:12.103
In fact,
I fought for you.

33:12.187 --> 33:13.821
You may have thought
you were fighting for me,

33:13.939 --> 33:15.940
but I know that Jessica
dumped me on Harvey,

33:16.074 --> 33:18.693
and it seems that the second
you made name partner,

33:18.777 --> 33:20.244
Harvey did the same thing
to you.

33:23.198 --> 33:25.450
Oh, you didn't know that,
did you?

33:25.534 --> 33:27.869
Then maybe we were
meant for each other,

33:27.953 --> 33:30.288
since we're both
left out of the club.

33:39.014 --> 33:40.181
You betrayed me.

33:40.299 --> 33:42.099
You make this big speech
about repairing our friendship,

33:42.184 --> 33:43.134
and all it was
was more words.

33:43.218 --> 33:44.135
What are you
talking about?

33:44.219 --> 33:46.020
You convinced me
to take Joan,

33:46.138 --> 33:47.772
while conveniently
leaving out the fact

33:47.856 --> 33:50.641
you're doing Harvey a favor.

33:50.776 --> 33:51.976
That's not why
I did it, Louis.

33:52.060 --> 33:54.228
Well, just tell me right now,
can he stand her?

33:54.313 --> 33:55.813
No, but he was
gonna keep her

33:55.948 --> 33:56.981
because you--

33:57.115 --> 33:58.149
Hurt his precious feelings.
I know.

33:58.283 --> 33:59.150
I felt so awful
about that.

33:59.234 --> 34:00.514
You know what, Louis?
You should.

34:00.536 --> 34:02.069
And while you're at it,
you should feel pretty awful

34:02.154 --> 34:03.514
about being a dick to me
right now.

34:03.622 --> 34:04.622
You lied to me again.

34:04.623 --> 34:07.158
No, Louis.
I fought for you...again.

34:07.292 --> 34:08.292
No.

34:08.293 --> 34:09.494
You made Joan
sound important.

34:09.661 --> 34:11.301
"The first client
that Jessica gave Harvey

34:11.413 --> 34:12.496
when he made name partner."

34:12.581 --> 34:13.998
She is important, Louis,
but you can't see that

34:14.132 --> 34:15.216
because you didn't
want a client.

34:15.333 --> 34:17.001
You just wanted to take
something away from Harvey.

34:17.135 --> 34:18.002
What I want is respect.

34:18.085 --> 34:19.219
Then get out of your own way

34:19.338 --> 34:21.839
and get on the goddamn team.

34:23.592 --> 34:25.141
You mean the team that kept
Mike's secret from me?

34:25.260 --> 34:26.310
No, Louis!

34:26.395 --> 34:28.228
I mean the team that
protected its own,

34:28.347 --> 34:30.898
because that's
what teams do.

34:32.400 --> 34:33.900
And, you know, I shouldn't
even be telling you this

34:34.018 --> 34:35.099
because she
wasn't going to,

34:35.187 --> 34:36.404
but if you need
a little bit more evidence

34:36.522 --> 34:37.989
of what we do
for each other,

34:38.106 --> 34:38.989
then take a look at Rachel,

34:39.107 --> 34:40.408
because she got
Katrina a job.

34:40.525 --> 34:41.576
- What?
- That's right.

34:41.693 --> 34:43.077
Your former associate,

34:43.195 --> 34:45.362
and you've been treating
Rachel like shit.

34:45.496 --> 34:46.914
So, if you're done
yelling at me,

34:47.032 --> 34:49.083
then I suggest you go fix
one of the thousand things

34:49.201 --> 34:50.501
that you have
screwed up lately,

34:50.619 --> 34:54.621
because the rest of us,
we are done fighting for you.

35:02.836 --> 35:05.705
[indistinct chatter]

35:08.175 --> 35:09.542
(man)
Mr. Ross.

35:09.710 --> 35:10.750
(Mike)
Ah, you must be Ian.

35:10.844 --> 35:12.244
And, please,
don't call me Mr. Ross.

35:12.262 --> 35:13.546
- Mike is fine.
- Ah, sure.

35:13.680 --> 35:15.348
Hey, thanks
for your call, Mike.

35:15.466 --> 35:17.050
Pearson Specter
is a great firm.

35:17.184 --> 35:18.601
Ah, well, you're
a great candidate.

35:18.719 --> 35:20.386
I'm a little curious why
you're still interviewing.

35:20.521 --> 35:22.271
I heard you had
a solid offer at Skadden.

35:22.389 --> 35:25.058
I do, but Skadden Arps
is no Pearson Specter.

35:25.142 --> 35:26.442
[laughs]
Are you sure it's not

35:26.560 --> 35:28.561
because you're worried
they'll find out that you failed

35:28.645 --> 35:30.363
Professor Gerard's
legal ethics class?

35:30.447 --> 35:32.482
- What?
- Oh, shit.

35:32.566 --> 35:33.566
You don't know.

35:33.567 --> 35:35.034
He hasn't changed
your grade,

35:35.119 --> 35:38.121
but he still has
your $25,000.

35:38.238 --> 35:39.405
[sighs]

35:39.540 --> 35:40.406
Who the hell are you?

35:40.491 --> 35:41.824
I'm exactly
who I said I was.

35:41.909 --> 35:42.909
The only thing I left out

35:42.910 --> 35:44.794
is that Professor Gerard
is my client.

35:44.912 --> 35:46.629
Well, he can't be
in trouble for this.

35:46.747 --> 35:47.747
I'd know.

35:47.748 --> 35:48.748
He's not.

35:48.832 --> 35:50.133
He's being accused
of accepting a bribe

35:50.250 --> 35:51.751
while conducting
a federal mediation

35:51.835 --> 35:53.169
because of this.

35:53.303 --> 35:54.387
That's not my problem.

35:54.471 --> 35:55.638
It's your problem now,

35:55.756 --> 35:58.257
which is why you're
gonna sign this.

36:01.011 --> 36:02.011
What is that?

36:02.012 --> 36:03.062
It's a sworn affidavit

36:03.147 --> 36:05.531
stating the money that
you paid Gerard is a loan.

36:07.935 --> 36:09.318
Well, what happens
to my grade?

36:09.436 --> 36:11.320
It stays the same
because Henry Gerard

36:11.438 --> 36:13.523
doesn't take money
to change grades.

36:13.607 --> 36:14.941
That's bullshit.
We had a deal.

36:15.025 --> 36:17.360
Yeah, well, consider this your
first lesson in the real world.

36:17.444 --> 36:19.028
Deals change.

36:19.113 --> 36:21.781
I don't care
what world it is.

36:21.915 --> 36:23.416
I'm not signing anything.

36:23.500 --> 36:24.500
That's too bad,

36:24.501 --> 36:26.619
because the truth
will come out.

36:26.753 --> 36:28.921
And this way,
you're failing a class

36:29.006 --> 36:30.339
instead of getting thrown
out of school

36:30.457 --> 36:32.058
for bribing a professor.

36:32.159 --> 36:33.543
It's up to you, Ian.

36:33.627 --> 36:34.677
You want an F,

36:34.795 --> 36:36.929
or do you want to not have
a legal career at all?

36:44.271 --> 36:47.306
(Gerard) So I sign this, and the
bribery allegations are gone?

36:47.441 --> 36:50.309
And no one ever
knows a thing.

36:50.444 --> 36:53.729
But I still have to pay
Ian back the money.

36:53.814 --> 36:55.581
That's the way
loans work.

36:55.716 --> 36:57.517
You say that like
I am a monster.

36:57.618 --> 36:59.452
I say it like it's true.

37:02.489 --> 37:05.074
You know...

37:05.209 --> 37:07.994
you never let me tell you
what the money was for.

37:08.078 --> 37:10.429
You didn't listen to me
when I told you I don't care.

37:10.564 --> 37:11.731
Who's the monster now?

37:11.832 --> 37:13.599
I don't care
because you always said

37:13.700 --> 37:16.586
the circumstances
don't matter.

37:16.720 --> 37:18.480
Well, do you care
that after Mike grilled me,

37:18.555 --> 37:19.755
I was so impressed with him

37:19.890 --> 37:21.507
that I wonder why
I'd forgotten him.

37:21.642 --> 37:24.844
So I looked through
my old records,

37:24.978 --> 37:26.679
just to see how he did,

37:26.813 --> 37:29.098
but I couldn't find
any record of him

37:29.233 --> 37:31.317
ever being in my class.

37:31.401 --> 37:33.236
Just like they're not
gonna find any record

37:33.353 --> 37:35.771
of you accepting a bribe
from a student.

37:35.906 --> 37:38.191
[chuckles]

37:38.325 --> 37:39.408
You saying we're even?

37:39.526 --> 37:41.110
I'm saying you got
a two-for-one,

37:41.195 --> 37:42.662
because they're also
not gonna find any record

37:42.746 --> 37:44.080
of you gambling last year.

37:44.198 --> 37:46.532
That's why you came to see me
back then, isn't it?

37:46.667 --> 37:49.035
You didn't want anyone
to find out about him.

37:49.119 --> 37:50.503
I'm not gonna tell you
why I came

37:50.587 --> 37:52.421
to see you last year,
Henry,

37:52.539 --> 37:55.007
because the circumstances
don't matter.

37:55.092 --> 37:56.876
[laughs]

37:57.010 --> 38:00.630
You really did pay
attention in my class.

38:00.714 --> 38:03.933
A lot more than you think.

38:04.051 --> 38:06.519
I'm sorry I let you down,
Mr. Specter.

38:10.891 --> 38:12.642
Professor...

38:14.895 --> 38:17.230
Don't worry about
paying back that loan.

38:17.397 --> 38:18.731
I got it.

38:18.899 --> 38:21.734
[melancholy guitar music]

38:21.902 --> 38:29.742
♪ ♪

38:59.740 --> 39:00.823
Louis...

39:00.941 --> 39:02.658
what can I do for you?

39:02.776 --> 39:04.327
The question isn't what
you can do for me, Jeff,

39:04.444 --> 39:05.778
but it's a matter
of what you're gonna do,

39:05.912 --> 39:07.496
which is cut the bullshit
right now.

39:07.614 --> 39:09.498
- What?
- You heard me.

39:09.616 --> 39:11.250
I know Jessica told you
about Hardman.

39:11.368 --> 39:12.368
Yeah, she did tell me,

39:12.452 --> 39:14.132
and I have refrained
from coming to see you

39:14.171 --> 39:15.788
about blackmailing her
out of courtesy.

39:15.922 --> 39:17.089
Courtesy?

39:17.174 --> 39:19.925
You haven't so much as
wished me a congratulations.

39:20.043 --> 39:21.127
You want me to kiss
the ring, Louis,

39:21.261 --> 39:22.261
after what you did?

39:22.296 --> 39:23.296
You're damn right I do,

39:23.347 --> 39:25.348
because I don't care
how it got up there.

39:25.465 --> 39:27.183
My name is on that wall.

39:27.301 --> 39:31.971
And if I had
a crowbar handy...

39:32.105 --> 39:33.222
I would pry it off.

39:33.307 --> 39:34.640
Well, Jeff, you don't.

39:34.725 --> 39:36.309
So the question you got
to ask yourself is,

39:36.393 --> 39:38.477
"Do you want to stick
with the team?"

39:38.562 --> 39:40.229
Because my name
is up there to stay

39:40.314 --> 39:41.647
whether you like it
or not.

39:41.782 --> 39:49.655
♪ ♪

40:06.089 --> 40:08.974
[indistinct chatter]

40:15.399 --> 40:17.149
Hey.

40:17.234 --> 40:19.518
Thanks for meeting me.

40:19.653 --> 40:21.604
What's going on?

40:21.688 --> 40:24.690
I wanted to thank you
for making me take Gerard.

40:26.493 --> 40:27.493
What happened?

40:27.494 --> 40:28.661
What makes you think
something happened?

40:28.779 --> 40:30.112
Because I know you,

40:30.247 --> 40:31.864
and I know you don't have
moments of self-reflection,

40:32.032 --> 40:33.165
let alone have a drink
with someone

40:33.283 --> 40:35.835
to tell them about it
unless something happened.

40:35.919 --> 40:37.503
You know what?
Something did happen.

40:37.587 --> 40:38.704
I dealt with some shit,

40:38.839 --> 40:40.373
and I'm trying
to thank you for it

40:40.507 --> 40:43.709
because it turned out
to be a good thing.

40:43.844 --> 40:46.178
I think the word you're
looking for is "closure."

40:46.263 --> 40:47.263
That's your word.

40:47.264 --> 40:48.214
The word I'm looking for is,

40:48.348 --> 40:49.382
"You're welcome, Harvey.

40:49.516 --> 40:51.133
That's nice of you to say."

40:51.268 --> 40:53.552
Thanks, Harvey.

40:53.637 --> 40:55.054
Good.

40:55.188 --> 40:56.222
Now listen to me.

40:56.356 --> 40:57.476
For a minute there,
I thought

40:57.524 --> 40:59.225
you were gonna tell me
that he knows.

40:59.309 --> 41:00.726
What?

41:00.811 --> 41:02.144
Maybe I'm crazy,

41:02.229 --> 41:05.314
but when I was prepping him,
for a second, he looked at me,

41:05.449 --> 41:07.316
and I thought,

41:07.451 --> 41:09.702
"He's suspicious."

41:09.786 --> 41:11.036
And then you called,

41:11.121 --> 41:13.406
and after everything
that's happened already, I--

41:13.573 --> 41:15.040
[sighs]

41:16.743 --> 41:20.079
It's fine, Mike.
He doesn't know.

41:20.213 --> 41:28.087
♪ ♪

